          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Public Funds for Public Schools Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to require the amount of a taxpayer's deductible charitable contributions to be reduced to account for the benefits of state income tax credits and deductions provided by a state to the taxpayer for a contribution to a specified school voucher organization. </p> <p>A &quot;specified school voucher organization&quot; is an organization with the primary purpose of providing vouchers, scholarships, or other funds for the expenses of students to attend elementary or secondary schools. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-11-07T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
